they want to learn how to play.

00:15:16.890 --> 00:15:20.050
So there's a lot of
interest in these camps

00:15:20.050 --> 00:15:21.350
where you go and you learn.

00:15:21.350 --> 00:15:23.240
And they come to Louisiana, they
retire there, and they dance.

00:15:23.240 --> 00:15:26.540
And some of them try to tell you
what you're doing isn't right

00:15:26.540 --> 00:15:27.840
and all that.

00:15:27.840 --> 00:15:29.140
But that's beside the point.

00:15:29.140 --> 00:15:30.940
They have a better way.

00:15:30.940 --> 00:15:33.680
But that's, I think that's
the popularity of it.

00:15:33.680 --> 00:15:37.830
The kids, at home, there's, you
know, you go to the festival

00:15:37.830 --> 00:15:40.110
at Cayenne at Lafayette, and
there's all these people,

00:15:40.110 --> 00:15:42.210
they play, and their good.

00:15:42.210 --> 00:15:44.360
They don't sing very
well, I don't think.

00:15:44.360 --> 00:15:45.660
But they play.

00:15:45.660 --> 00:15:46.960
It used to be just accordions.

00:15:46.960 --> 00:15:50.080 position:56%
Because apparently an accordion is a
little easier to play than a violin.

00:15:50.080 --> 00:15:51.920
Now it's all violins and
fewer accordion players.

00:15:51.920 --> 00:15:54.860
It's really interesting
how it does that.

00:15:54.860 --> 00:15:56.440
So, you know.

00:15:56.440 --> 00:15:57.740
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:15:57.740 --> 00:15:59.950
&gt;&gt; So I don't think, you're
not going to lose the music.

00:15:59.950 --> 00:16:01.250
